Governor Abubakar Atiku Bagudu has directed the Public Works Agency under the Chairmanship of Alhaji Bello Dantani ( Magajin Rafin Kabi ) to embark on renovation of the Dadin Kowa Market in Maiyama Local Government area which was razed by fire recently. This was disclosed to newsmen in Birnin Kebbi this Tuesday by Alhaji Bello Dantani ( Magajin Rafin Kabi). He said already stakeholders of the local Government and the affected victims have met on the issue to ensure involvement of those concerned in the local Government. Senate Moves To Protect Witnesses In Corruption Cases Anyim Respects All Religions — Coalition Of Northern… Magajin Rafi added that engineers from the state ministry of Works have been mobilised to the market in compliance with the directives of the governor to ensure prompt action. It will be recalled that Governor Abubakar Atiku Bagudu was in Dadin Kowa market on Sunday to assess the level of destruction caused by fire and sympathise with the victims.